INSTALL
-------

   *) To install the precompiled binaries into `/usr/local' run
      `make install-pre'

      To change the place where CthughaNix will be installed to you have to 
      edit the `Makefile'.

      The precompiled binaries are optimized for i486.
      

   *) To compile your own version of CthughaNix:
      
      1) run `./configure'
	 For a list of possible options use './configure --help'. See Note 1.
	 
      2) run `make'
	 This will produce all the necessary files. Depending on what compiler
	 you use, you might get some warnings, which you can ignore.

      3) run `make install'
	 to install CthughaNix on your system. 


Note 1:  The only option of 'configure' that is not self explaining 
     is the --with-arch=ARCH option. This option is mainly to distinguish
     between pentiumpro and amdk6.
     Possible value for ARCH are 386, 486, pentium, pentiumpro, amdk6
     With --without-cpu you disable any processor specifiy optimization.




Problems
--------
   * A problem (I have it sometimes) with shared libraries is, that you
     don't have the "library without version number".  For example if
     you have `libXaw.so.6' and *no* `libXaw.so' you should add a link
     with
                    ln -s libXaw.so.6 libXaw.so

     You should add such links for all your shared libraries.

   * If you have problems with the sound reading you should try the option 
     `--snd-method'. Using a value of 1 or 2 might solve your problem.
     Please tell me if you continue to have problems (or even know how to fix
     it)

   * Please take a look at the `TODO' file for known bugs and problems. 



Non-Linux-Machines
------------------
   * This release of CthughaNix that should also work on some machines
     not running Linux. You may not have any sound, but you can try
     something like `--play /dev/audio --silent'. 

   * Please tell me if you run this version on a different operating
     system. And please tell me also what you had to change to make it 
     running.

   * The network code might not even compile on non-Linux machines.
     Use the configure option `--without-network' to disable all network
     stuff.

